Package org.ivoa.dm.stc.coords

Class ContinuousAxis

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ivoa.dm.stc.coords.Axis
      • org.ivoa.dm.stc.coords.ContinuousAxis
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulations, org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<java.lang.Long>
    @Entity
@VoDml(id="coords:ContinuousAxis",
       role=objectType)
public class ContinuousAxis
extends Axis
implements org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<java.lang.Long>
    Axis description for continuous data. This object describes the domain for a particular axis of the domain space. It allows for the specification of the legal domain range (min,max), and a flag indicating if the axis is cyclic. objectType: ContinuousAxis

        public ContinuousAxis​(org.ivoa.dm.ivoa.Quantity domainMin,
                      org.ivoa.dm.ivoa.Quantity domainMax,
                      java.lang.Boolean cyclic,
                      java.lang.String name)
        full parameter constructor.
        Parameters:
        domainMin - Minimum extent of the axis domain space. If not provided, the domain space is considered to have no lower bound (-INFINITY).
        domainMax - Maximum extent of the axis domain space. If not provided, the domain space is considered to have no upper bound (+INFINITY).
        cyclic - Flag indicating if the axis is cyclic in nature. If not provided, it is assumed to be FALSE.
        name - Freeform string, provides the name or label for the axis.
